The paper discusses deep reinforcement learning methods for multi-agent domains, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on multi-agent coordination suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of actor-critic methods and ensemble policies suggests a focus on optimization and control (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY).
